son.param_description:
User Levels, different interception strategies can be configured for users of different levels. Available values: 
0: Lowest level users, typically including newly registered, completely inactive, or level 0 users, etc.;
1: Lower level users, typically including low active or low level users, etc.;
2: Medium level users, typically including users with certain activity or medium level, etc.;
3: Higher level users, typically including highly active or high level users, etc.;
4: Highest level users, typically including paying users, VIP users, etc.

When riskLevel is PASS, return normal;
In other cases, display in the format: "First Level Label: Second Level Label: Third Level Label" in Chinese.
This is only for human reference to understand the reasons for the risk, and the program should not rely on the value of this parameter for logical processing.

